---
description: Admin pages must enforce admin or storyteller access using includes/verify_role.php and redirect unauthorized users to login.php
globs: admin/**/*.php
alwaysApply: false
---

- **Admin UI pages MUST require authentication and verified privileges**
  - Start the session (or ensure it is started).
  - Include DB connection.
  - Verify role against the database (prevents session tampering).
  - Redirect to `login.php` if the user is not authorized.

- **Canonical privilege verification**
  - Use [V:\includes\verify_role.php](mdc:includes/verify_role.php):
    - `verifyUserRole($conn, $user_id)`
    - `isAdminUser($user_role)` (admin OR storyteller)

```php
<?php
require_once __DIR__ . '/../includes/connect.php';

if (session_status() === PHP_SESSION_NONE) {
    session_start();
}

$user_id = (int)($_SESSION['user_id'] ?? 0);
if ($user_id <= 0) {
    header('Location: ../login.php');
    exit;
}

require_once __DIR__ . '/../includes/verify_role.php';
$user_role = verifyUserRole($conn, $user_id);
if (!isAdminUser($user_role)) {
    header('Location: ../login.php');
    exit;
}
```

- **Admin API endpoints MUST apply the same authorization gate**
  - Use the same role verification logic before any data reads/writes.
